postcontent: I have for sale a beautiful circa 1984 Smith & Wesson Model 36 (no dash) nickel-plated snub nose .38 Special steel revolver that is in wonderful condition. Even if you aren't interested in buying it, the pictures are worth looking at and that is free ;-)Designed to be small and compact for easy carry conceal or small storage areas, this Model 36 J-frame has a pinned 1.875 inch (sometimes called a 2 inch) barrel. It has 5-round capacity in a swing-out cylinder, case-hardened trigger, and case-hardened exposed hammer with single or double action. This gun has a grooved rear sight and a ramped fixed blade front sight. It features a bright shiny nickel finish and has Smith & Wesson wood grips.This thirty-two year old classic revolver is in beautiful condition. The original owner fired three cylinder's worth of rounds before storing it. I took it to the range after I bought it and fired thirty-five factory-manufactured rounds through it, keeping the total of the rounds fired through this gun at fifty.As with all of the S&W revolvers I have had the pleasure to shoot, this one is an accurate and fun gun. While this gun is pretty enough to just put up somewhere and admire, it is dependable and accurate enough to carry conceal or use as a house gun.There are a few very small light surface spots on this revolver from time in careful storage over the past more than three decades, but I am not sure any of them even show up in the non-retouched pictures.
